<li> @HI{{@EM{{sorenara}}}} ...
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@HI{{@EM{{sorenara}}}} is a conjunction used a the beginning of a sentence to refer to something
mentioned in a previous sentence. The meaning is "in that case".

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      A: @HI{{@KJ{{head}}ga@KJ{{pain}}iidesu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      B: @HI{{@EM{{sorenara}}sugu@KJ{{lie*down}}nasai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      A: I have a headache.
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      B: In that case, go to and lie down straightaway.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
The @HI{{sore}} in @HI{{@EM{{sorenara}}}} refers to something in a previous sentence. The @HI{{nara}} refers to the speaker's supposition regarding the truth of the previous statement.
</p>

<p>
@HI{{@EM{{sorenara}}}} has a more formal form @HI{{sorenaraba}}.
</p>

<p>
The sentence following @HI{{@EM{{sorenara}}}} is bound by the same restrictions that apply to @HI{{nara}}.
</p>

<p>
Unlike <a href="grammar-sore-dewa.html">@HI{{soredeha}}</a>, @HI{{@EM{{sorenara}}}} depends on a verbal context.
</p>

